net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc

Class DirContextSourceFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc.DirContextSourceFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObjectFactory

    public class DirContextSourceFactory
extends Object
implements ObjectFactory
    An object factory for creating DirContextSource instances backed by a DirContextSource.Builder. This factory should work in any servlet container with JNDI support, but was tested under Apache Tomcat 8.5.x only.

    Integration in your context.xml is as simple as: 

     <Context>
 [...]
   <!-- Add this -->
   <Resource name="ldap/localname" type="net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc.DirContextSource"
     factory="net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc.DirContextSourceFactory"
     urls="ldap://hostname ldap://another-hostname" />
 [...]
 </Context>
    For a complete reference, see documentation site.
    Version:
    $Id$
